sentences.t:
audacem faciebat amor. venit ecce recenti
caede leaena boum spumantis oblita rictus
depositura sitim vicini fontis in unda;

sentences.l:
Love was making her bold. Look — there comes, with a fresh
kill of oxen, a lioness, her foaming jaws besmeared,
about to lay down her thirst in the nearby spring's water;

sentences.t:
serius egressus vestigia vidit in alto
pulvere certa ferae totoque expalluit ore
Pyramus;

sentences.l:
Having come out later, he saw in the deep dust
the sure tracks of the beast, and over his whole face went pale,
Pyramus;

sentences.t:
Ecce metu nondum posito, ne fallat amantem,
illa redit iuvenemque oculis animoque requirit,
quantaque vitarit narrare pericula gestit;

sentences.l:
Look — her fear not yet laid aside, lest she fail her lover,
she returns and seeks the young man with eyes and heart,
and longs to tell what great dangers she escaped;

sentences.t:
vota tamen tetigere deos, tetigere parentes;
nam color in pomo est, ubi permaturuit, ater,
quodque rogis superest, una requiescit in urna.

sentences.l:
Yet their prayers touched the gods, touched the parents;
for the color in the fruit, when it has ripened, is black,
and what survives the pyres rests together in one urn.
